1) Checking out submodules

My server is crappy (a small router), so it will either die or be very slow when you try to clone the full tree from it. Please clone qemu and wine from git://source.winehq.org/git/wine.git and git://git.qemu.org/qemu.git and run

git submodule update --init --reference /local/path/to/wine wine
git submodule update --init --reference /local/path/to/qemu qemu

The local checkouts need to remain because .git/modules/{wine|qemu}/objects/info points there.

If you prefer to have the entire code inside this directory you can do
git clone git://git.qemu.org/qemu.git
git clone git://source.winehq.org/git/wine.git
git submodule update --init qemu    # Ignore "Direct fetching of that commit failed." error
git submodule update --init wine    # Ignore "Direct fetching of that commit failed." error
git submodule sync qemu
git submodule sync wine
git submodule update

This will clone the upstream projects, update the remote URL and check out the remaining parts from my server. Once the submodules are checked out you can use the normal git submodule workflow. My server should survive incremental fetches :-) .
